What I share with you now is something from a dream. I have long desired to pursue this particular vision and after much planning, logistics and weather coming together it worked! The moments of light and life captured here are simply exceptional… Before you get to excited please realize that this is an exposure blend. Both images were taken within thirty minutes of each other and within a mile or so of each other. First we found the dolphins and I spent a good deal of time swimming with the pod and shooting them with an underwater housing, it was simply incredible and very few words could describe the feelings I had being in the water surrounded with these magical beings! Not but a short time later and here we were driving a boat through this incredible seacave aglow from the morning sun! Some things simply cannot be explained to convey the magnitude of magic held within a space and time and for me, this is one of them, enjoy ~ ——————————————————————————————— #wildplaces #kauai #wildernessculture #kauailove #agameoftones #napalicoast #ohana #marlonholdenfineart #hawaiianislands #seacave———————————————————————————————

I lived in and among Tahiti, Moorea, Raitea, Taha’a and Bora Bora for the better part of a year. Returning here was like seeing a long lost family member all grown up. When I write I’m often in isolation with my thoughts. I realize many people simply like the pretty pictures much like the outer layer referred to as the candy coating, I’m an acquired taste as I do not fit the mold. My messages may only be read by the one percent and most likely only felt by much less than that, however the desire I have to make this about so much more than an image is near to my heart… I desire a deeper connection with myself, my work and all of you. Nature is my canvas and the camera is my means of capturing that canvas, however the paintbrush is within my soul. Merely documenting moments holds very little intrinsic value to me on they’re own. Where true expression begins is where I begin to create each vision within my mind, mixing parts photography and parts digital artistry to create a vision created unlike anything else… That is where I leave behind the rigidity of rules, the misconception that something should be anything other than what I choose to make it. Having traveled the world several times over, I have witnessed firsthand how convention is the destroyer of dreams and the darkness amongst the light. So with that I encourage you to be your own form of unique, your own form of dreamer. That you remember the day you were born you won the greatest lottery ticket possible. Don’t squander it worrying about what others are doing, focus on you and know just how incredible you really are! Have a wonderful day ~ ——————————————————————————————— #wildplaces #fallcolors #fall #autumn #ranchlife #colorado #marlonholdenfineart #treemagic #usinterior #telluride———————————————————————————————

Recently I had the opportunity to experience a truly remarkable and very early winter bloom in our Southern Deserts. All of the rains had left us with remarkable conditions to see a more profuse Verbena bloom than I had ever seen before! With clusters of pink flowers bigger than I had ever before seen in 30 years! This rare and remarkable moment was taken in one of our most remote wilderness areas, entirely untouched by most people let alone any photographers. It was a profound moment for me in all of my wildflower pursuits and I hope that you enjoy the resulting artwork in Gods beautiful creation… For those who have asked, this is not Death Valley, nor is it anywhere you can drive within 7.4 miles of ~ ———————————————————————————————— #wildflowers #usinterior #sandverbena #marlonholdenfineart #desertflowers #wilderness_culture  #superbloom #landscapephotographer ————————————————————————————————

It begins to sound funny when you speak about a twenty year bloom multiple times over. Yet I believe that when you’ve chased wildflower’s passionately for over twenty years I guess it’s bound to happen at some point or another… In either respect, I feel fortunate to have seen such a magical moment on this earth! While the crowds jostled for position, crowding around in parks, I decided to put my rigs four wheel drive to good use and venture many miles out into the Sonoran landscape. Here, there wasn’t a sound but birds and wind, saguaro cactuses and brilliant Mexican poppies scattered about with peak lupine blooms in every direction! The best part was in a week of shooting, there wasn’t a soul in sight! On this day the clouds were just perfect and the flowers were peak bloom having lost very few petals. I love Peak bloom, it is the ultimate form of crescendo in nature! For those interested, you can easily walk around these flowers without damaging them as they are a fair distance apart, not tight together which makes it nice while searching out your composition! I hope you enjoy ~ ———————————————————————————————— #wildflowers #usinterior #mexicanpoppies #marlonholdenfineart #desertflowers #wilderness_culture  #superbloom #landscapephotographer ————————————————————————————————

As children we are free to be dreamers, we are even encouraged to dream, yet once we are adults we are told to quit dreaming and be realistic... I’m not sure where we turned as a culture, society, as a race or as humanity; however photography was my way of pushing away the confines of what many have said is only a dream... My advice to myself has always been to be honorable to your life force and if you can dream it, you can achieve it! I left behind everything everyone said I shouldn’t leave to do something I shouldn’t do and I wouldn’t change a thing... Now they are the ones in silence looking at what only dreams can accomplish... So if what I do means anything to someone out in the world, I feel that it is okay to be different, to think different and most importantly, it is okay to dream bigger than any around you ~———————————————————————————————— #marlonholdenfineart #wilderness_culture #awesomeearth #landscapephotographer #fineartphotography #california ————————————————————————————————

By far my greatest pursuit is that of rare wildflower blooms! I seek them out and sometimes it takes decades to see such pursuits come to Fruition. I am quiet and often experience these places alone in silence to pay reverence to their existence in this moment. Just like life itself, reverent, timeless and beautiful yet fleeting. I never talk about where and I always post after they are long gone, simply because it is such a personal journey for me… Spending years and years waiting for these moments, this particular bloom I’ve watched patiently for 22 years and while there had been a mediocre bloom here and there, nothing like this had I ever seen… So with a full heart I share with you a quiet moment of my labors of love and might you enjoy it as much as I did ~ ———————————————————————————————— #wildflowers #usinterior #mexicanpoppies #lupine #marlonholdenfineart #desertflowers #wilderness_culture  #superbloom #landscapephotographer ————————————————————————————————

So on this day I set out on foot across the dunes with a few great friends @krl_photo @rootswalker @shainblumphotography and @felixalfarophotography to see what we could drum up! After hiking back and forth, searching within the tangles, we all lost ourselves attempting to capture our moments. Light was fading pretty quickly and on this evening we were very fortunate to actually have really great conditions with a perfect little hole above the mountains which light poured from as the sun gently set behind the distant range! As I scrambled back to the best composition I had found while scouting, I was lucky enough to capture these fleeting few seconds of light with that touch of brilliance to illuminate the scene! Stoked to have a shot from here finally with good light, it wasn’t without some challenging composition work but I think I’m satisfied with it! The best part of it all is the laughs and good company with truly great people!
